HEADWORD: Deutohydroguret
<hw>Deu`to*hy*drog"u*ret</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>deut-</ets>, <ets>deuto-</ets> + <ets>hydroguret</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A compound containing in the molecule two atoms
of hydrogen united with some other element or radical.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deutoplasm</ent>⟦br⟧
